Class ParameterTypeVisitor

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
ExpressionVisitor
Direct Known Subclasses:
DefaultParameterTypeVisitor, EclipseLinkParameterTypeVisitor
public class ParameterTypeVisitor
extends AbstractTraverseParentVisitor

This visitor's responsibility is to find the type of an input parameter.

Provisional API: This interface is part of an interim API that is still under development and expected to change significantly before reaching stability. It is available at this early stage to solicit feedback from pioneering adopters on the understanding that any code that uses this API will almost certainly be broken (repeatedly) as the API evolves.

Version:
2.4
Author:
Pascal Filion
Since:
2.3

Field Detail

currentExpression

protected Expression currentExpression
This is used to prevent an infinite loop between input parameters. Example: ":arg1 = :arg2".

expression

protected Expression expression
The Expression that will help to determine the type of the input parameter.

ignoreType

protected boolean ignoreType
Used to ignore the type when calculating it. If Object.class was used, then it could incorrectly calculate the type. Example: ":arg = 'JPQL' AND :arg IS NULL", the second :arg should be ignored.

inputParameter

protected InputParameter inputParameter
The InputParameter for which its type will be searched by visiting the query.

queryContext

protected final JPQLQueryContext queryContext
The context used to query information about the query.

type

protected java.lang.Class<?> type
The well defined type, which does not have to be calculated.
